## Basic Usage (Free Version)

### Import Pattern

```typescript
// 1. Import the HugeiconsIcon component
import { HugeiconsIcon } from '@hugeicons/react';

// 2. Import icon objects from the free icons package
import { 
  Analytics01Icon,
  ArrowDown01Icon,
  Delete02Icon,
  Activity01Icon,
  Layout01Icon,
  UserIcon,
  UserGroupIcon,
} from '@hugeicons/core-free-icons';
```

### Icon Props

The `HugeiconsIcon` component supports the following props:

```typescript
interface HugeIconProps {
  icon: IconObject;        // REQUIRED: Icon object from @hugeicons/core-free-icons
  size?: number;           // Size in pixels (default: 24)
  color?: string;          // Icon color (default: currentColor)
  strokeWidth?: number;    // Stroke width (default: 1.5)
  className?: string;      // Additional CSS classes
  onClick?: () => void;    // Click handler
  style?: CSSProperties;   // Inline styles
}
```

### Examples

```tsx
import { HugeiconsIcon } from '@hugeicons/react';
import { 
  Search01Icon, 
  Delete02Icon, 
  Analytics01Icon,
  Settings01Icon 
} from '@hugeicons/core-free-icons';

// ✅ Basic icon with size and color
<HugeiconsIcon icon={Search01Icon} size={20} color="currentColor" />

// ✅ Using Tailwind classes (recommended)
<HugeiconsIcon 
  icon={Delete02Icon}
  className="text-red-400 hover:text-red-300 cursor-pointer"
  size={18}
/>

// ✅ Custom stroke width
<HugeiconsIcon 
  icon={Analytics01Icon}
  size={24}
  strokeWidth={2}
  className="text-blue-400"
/>

// ✅ With click handler
<HugeiconsIcon
  icon={Settings01Icon}
  size={20}
  className="text-gray-400 hover:text-gray-200 transition-colors cursor-pointer"
  onClick={() => console.log('Settings clicked')}
/>
```

