## Best Practices

### ✅ Do

- Use `currentColor` or Tailwind text classes for color
- Match icon size to surrounding text
- Use consistent stroke widths (1.5 or 2)
- Add hover states for interactive icons
- Include `cursor-pointer` for clickable icons
- Use transitions for smooth color changes
- Provide semantic meaning (not just decoration)

### ❌ Don't

- Don't use inline styles for colors (use Tailwind)
- Don't make icons too large (overwhelms UI)
- Don't use different stroke widths inconsistently
- Don't forget to add hover states on interactive icons
- Don't use too many different icons (visual clutter)
- Don't sacrifice accessibility (add aria-labels if needed)

